Sentencas: Although La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 (LSCF) owns a high level of maturity as a cathode material for intermediate and high-temperature SOFCs, there still exists tremendous potential for it to be employed under an efficient low temperature working conditions.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: Since the charge transfer and oxygen ions diffusion act as pivotal obstacles to realizing the operation of LT-SOFCs (below 600 degrees C), the B-site doping elements (Ni, Cu, Nb) in commercial LSCF are selected using the first-principles calculation.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: Based on the theoretical findings, the novel Cu-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xCuxO3 (LSCFCx, x = 0, 0.1, 0.2) cathode materials are synthesized with exploring the phase structure, valence states of the elements, and thermogravimetric properties.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: Among different doping elements, Cu doping could facilitate the electrochemical performance of LSCFCx cathode by the enhancement of electrons at B-site and enrichment the of oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: Arising from the inspiring charge transfer and the accelerating oxygen ion transportation, Cu-substitution yields superior activity than other LSCF doping elements.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: The polarization resistant and activation energy values for LSCFC0.2 cathode attenuates more than 71% and 35% in contrast to the undoped LSCF cathode, respectively.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: The maximal power density of the anode-supported single cells utilizing LSCFC0.2 cathode outputs 0.594 W center dot cm-2 at 600 degrees C and promotes over 41% than commercial LSCF at the same condition.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion

Sentencas: These results conclusively point to a practical Cu-doping strategy for the development of highly efficient cathodes for LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Alternative B-site-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xMxO3 (M = Ni, Cu, Nb; x=0, 0.1, 0.2) as innovative cathode material for LT-SOFC with enhanced charge transfer and oxygen ion diffusion
